# Plot the decision boundary. For that, we will assign a color to each (Training Data)
# point in the mesh [x_min, x_max]x[y_min, y_max].
x_min, x_max = X1_train[:, 0].min() - .5, X1_train[:, 0].max() + .5
y_min, y_max = X1_train[:, 1].min() - .5, X1_train[:, 1].max() + .5
h = .02  # step size in the mesh
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x_min, x_max, h), np.arange(y_min, y_max, h))
Z = le_model.predict(np.c_[xx.ravel(), yy.ravel()])

# Put the result into a color plot

Z = Z.reshape(xx.shape)
plt.figure(1, figsize=(12, 8))
plt.pcolormesh(xx, yy, Z, cmap=plt.cm.Paired)
